+## 3. Data flow
+```
+runOrchestrator(numCtx = router ctx)
+  â†’ withRootDelegationContext(numCtx)         root frame carries the orchestrator's budget
+    â†’ orchestrator.generateText
+      â†’ delegate_to_X.execute
+        â†’ withDelegationSpan(X)                tags delegation.depth=1, ancestors="X"
+          â†’ checkDelegation(X)                 ambient depth 0 â†’ ok (depth-only; recursion allowed)
+          â†’ callerNumCtx = ctx.numCtx          = orchestrator's budget
+          â†’ runInDelegationContext(X, Xctx){depth1,[X],numCtx:Xctx}
+            â†’ runDefinedAgent(X)               (if X delegates to Y: caps Y's return by Xctx)
+          â†’ return { text: concise(text, callerNumCtx) }   cap = Â¼ Ã— orchestrator ctx Ã— 4 chars/token
+```
+A delegation that would make `depth + 1 > 5` returns `{ error }` (soft) + emits `agent.guardrail.violation`. Repeated agent names are NOT rejected â€” depth is the bound. Each return is capped against **its consumer's** live `num_ctx`.
+
